{
  "stem": "1873.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Sometimes they grabbed five, six people, took them to the cemetery, and killed them there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And we understood that the Jews had no rights, without any protection.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Izbica was not a ghetto as we imagine a ghetto-- Warsaw, [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Krakow. ?] Because the whole town was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Only the burgermeister was a Pole.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "The chief of police was a Pole, chief of the post office.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So there was no need to, to put a section of the town as a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "The whole, the whole town was regarded as a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "We had no barbed wires.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "But we weren't allowed to go outside the town.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "If you were caught outside, you was immediately killed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Polish police, of course, did help, working with the Nazis in this regard, checking the Jews.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Nevertheless, there was no hunger in our place, because we were able still to mingle with the Poles, go out to the villages, you know, and buy some food.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We weren't allowed, so we were risking with our lives.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Some were shot.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we did know our ways.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And not too many people were killed because of smuggling food.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was going on for a while.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Of course, the Nazis once in a while went in the-- I will call it ghetto-- went in where the Jews used to live, and grabbed 100 people, 200, took them to some special project, like building an airstrip or road.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And after the project was finished-- took a month or five weeks-- they let them back to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was some beating going on at this camp, but nevertheless, people did return.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Everybody was obligated to go to the working camps in turn.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
